# Task: Migrate DOM refs to useTemplateRef() across 6 frontend files
## Description
<user_task_content>
## Overview
<recommendation_content>
## Goal

Replace the legacy `ref<HTMLElement | null>(null)` pattern with Vue 3.5's `useTemplateRef()` API across all 9 DOM ref instances in 6 files. The template `ref="..."` attributes stay unchanged. Only the script setup changes.

## Files to Change

### 1. `frontend/src/features/auth/ui/LoginPage.vue` (line 15)

```typescript
// Before
import { ref, computed, nextTick } from 'vue';
const pinInputRef = ref<HTMLInputElement | null>(null);

// After
import { ref, computed, nextTick, useTemplateRef } from 'vue';
const pinInputRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLInputElement>('pinInputRef');
```

All usages of `pinInputRef.value?.focus()` stay the same — no other changes needed.

### 2. `frontend/src/features/auth/ui/RegisterPage.vue` (line 15)

Same change as LoginPage:
```typescript
// Before
import { ref, computed, nextTick } from 'vue';
const pinInputRef = ref<HTMLInputElement | null>(null);

// After
import { ref, computed, nextTick, useTemplateRef } from 'vue';
const pinInputRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLInputElement>('pinInputRef');
```

### 3. `frontend/src/features/ai-chat/ui/AiChatPage.vue` (line 18)

```typescript
// Before
const chatContainer = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);

// After
const chatContainer = useTemplateRef<HTMLElement>('chatContainer');
```

Add `useTemplateRef` to the vue import. Template has `ref="chatContainer"` — no change needed.

### 4. `frontend/src/features/user-settings/ui/UserSettingsPage.vue` (line 38)

```typescript
// Before
const addPasskeyButtonRef = ref<HTMLButtonElement | null>(null);

// After
const addPasskeyButtonRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLButtonElement>('addPasskeyButtonRef');
```

### 5. `frontend/src/features/org-settings/ui/OrgSettingsPage.vue` (lines 26-28)

```typescript
// Before
const dialogRef = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);
const cancelBtnRef = ref<HTMLButtonElement | null>(null);
const triggerRef = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);

// After
const dialogRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLElement>('dialogRef');
const cancelBtnRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLButtonElement>('cancelBtnRef');
const triggerRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLElement>('triggerRef');
```

### 6. `frontend/src/widgets/app-layout/ui/OrgSwitcher.vue` (lines 9-16)

This file has two refs: a simple button ref and a v-for list ref. The v-for variant also needs the `setItemRef` helper removed.

```typescript
// Before
import { ref, nextTick, type ComponentPublicInstance } from 'vue';
const triggerRef = ref<HTMLButtonElement | null>(null);
const itemRefs = ref<HTMLLIElement[]>([]);

function setItemRef(el: Element | ComponentPublicInstance | null, index: number) {
  if (el instanceof HTMLLIElement) {
    itemRefs.value[index] = el;
  }
}

// After
import { ref, nextTick, useTemplateRef } from 'vue';
const triggerRef = useTemplateRef<HTMLButtonElement>('triggerRef');
const itemRefs = useTemplateRef<HTMLLIElement[]>('itemRefs');
// Remove the setItemRef function entirely
```

In the template, change the `<li>` ref:
```html
<!-- Before -->
<li :ref="(el) => setItemRef(el, index)" ...>

<!-- After -->
<li ref="itemRefs" ...>
```

Update array access to use optional chaining (since `useTemplateRef` value can be null before mount):
```typescript
// Before
itemRefs.value[focusedIndex.value]?.focus();
itemRefs.value[next]?.focus();
itemRefs.value[prev]?.focus();

// After
itemRefs.value?.[focusedIndex.value]?.focus();
itemRefs.value?.[next]?.focus();
itemRefs.value?.[prev]?.focus();
```

Also remove `ComponentPublicInstance` from the import since it's no longer used.

## Acceptance Criteria

- All 9 `ref<HTML*Element | null>(null)` / `ref<HTML*Element[]>([])` DOM refs replaced with `useTemplateRef()`
- `setItemRef` helper function removed from OrgSwitcher.vue
- `ComponentPublicInstance` import removed from OrgSwitcher.vue
- All existing tests pass (`npm test -w frontend`)
- TypeScript compiles without errors (`vue-tsc --noEmit`)
- OrgSwitcher keyboard navigation still works (arrow keys, Enter, Escape)
</recommendation_content>

## Context
- **Category:** refactor
- **Priority Score:** 7/10
- **Estimated Complexity:** low

## Reasoning
<recommendation_content>
Vue 3.5 (stable, currently `vue@3.5.30`) introduced `useTemplateRef()` as the canonical API for typed DOM refs. It provides better type inference (no manual `| null` annotations needed), supports dynamic ref bindings, and simplifies the v-for case by eliminating the `setItemRef` callback pattern. The OrgSwitcher cleanup removes 5 lines of boilerplate. All 6 files are independent — no shared state between them. This is a pure refactor with zero behavior change.
</recommendation_content>
</user_task_content>

## Category: refactor

## Context
- Product: RSI Starter: Vue 3 Fullstack SaaS
- Purpose: Starter template maintained by RSI for new product scaffolding
- Deployed path: /opt/rsi-platform/repos/starter-vue3-fullstack
- Allowed domains: All domains (unrestricted)
